President Obama has nominated Marina Garcia Marmolejo to serve as a District Court Judge in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas. Marmolejo is currently a partner at the law firm Reid Davis, where she has been since 2009. Prior to that, she was Of Counsel at Thompson & Knight's San Antonio Office from 2007 to 2009. Marmolejo has also served as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of Texas from 1999 to 2007. She began her legal career as an Assistant Federal Public Defender in the Western and Southern Districts of Texas. Marmolejo holds a J.D. from St. Mary's University School of Law, an M.A. from St. Mary's University Graduate School, and a B.A. from the University of the Incarnate Word.